Clerk of Taraba State House of Assembly, Orngu Mellah has threatened legal action against a social media post accussing him of complicity in the ongoing feud between the Tiv and Jukun in the state.<img class="size-full wp-image-1222101 aligncenter" src="https://i0.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/reps.jpg?resize=640%2C419&#038;ssl=1" alt="" width="640" height="419" srcset="https://i0.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/reps.jpg?w=1500&amp;ssl=1 1500w, https://i0.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/reps.jpg?resize=300%2C197&amp;ssl=1 300w, https://i0.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/reps.jpg?resize=768%2C503&amp;ssl=1 768w, https://i0.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/reps.jpg?resize=1024%2C671&amp;ssl=1 1024w, https://i0.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/reps.jpg?resize=58%2C38&amp;ssl=1 58w, https://i0.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/reps.jpg?resize=260%2C170&amp;ssl=1 260w, https://i0.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/reps.jpg?resize=198%2C130&amp;ssl=1 198w, https://i0.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/reps.jpg?resize=560%2C367&amp;ssl=1 560w, https://i0.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/reps.jpg?w=1280&amp;ssl=1 1280w" sizes="(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px" data-recalc-dims="1" /> Mellah who is a Tiv man, in a statement personally signed by him, gave seven days ultimatum for the retraction of the publication, which he said was published by Tsokwa Fwaje Jezreel on social media. According to him, “the publication clearly intends to blackmail and cause mischief to my reputation and career as a civil servant and particularly as the clerk of the Taraba State House of Assembly. 21-year-old Ekiti University student convicted for cyber crime(Opens in a new browser tab) “The publication has attracted a lot of negative comments against me on social media and I wish to state categorically that I do not belong to any such group named in the publication.” In order to evade litigation, Mellah said the publisher of the malicious information must “retract his publication and tender an unreserved apology to me which must be published on all platforms he made such publications in addition to three national dalies.” However,  Vanguard’s check on Jezreel’s Facebook page which Mellah mentioned as one of the platforms used for circulating the information, reveals that the said post titled “Re-strategizing? Tiv elites hold emergency meeting in Orngu Mela’s residence in Jalingo” was accompanied with a photograph of cars parked in front of a building at press time. Vanguard President Muhammadu Buhari has given a marching order to the governments of Benue and Taraba States as well as their traditional rulers to bring to an end the hostility between the Tiv and Jukun people. August 31, 2019 In "News" Leaders of Tiv and Jukun tribes in Taraba state have commended president Muhamadu Buhari's initiative  to raise a committee that will bring an end to the persistent crisis between the Tiv and Jukun  tribes in the state. June 30, 2019 In "News" About 15 persons are said to have been killed in the crisis that broke out between Tiv and Jukun communities on the fringes of Taraba and Benue borders. April 5, 2019 In "News"